            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.5.0</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Jarvis is now signed and notarized by Apple — installing is just download, drag to Applications, and double-click. No Terminal, no "Open Anyway", no security dialogs.</li>
  <li>Jarvis keeps itself up to date: it checks for new versions automatically and offers them with one click (or use the Jarvis menu → Check for Updates…).</li>
  <li>Upgrading from an older build? Trash the old copy first, then grant Screen Recording &amp; Accessibility once more — macOS sees the new Apple signature as a fresh app. This is a one-time step; future updates keep your permissions.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
